epi-HAD-ah.def: We measure household solid fuels using the number of age-standardized disability-adjusted life-years lost per 100,000 persons (DALY rate) due to exposure to household air pollution (HAP) from the use of household solid fuels.
epi-HAD-ah.name: Household air pollution from solid fuels
epi-HAD-ah.source: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation

epi-OZD-ah.def: We measure ozone exposure using the number of age-standardized disability-adjusted life-years lost per 100,000 persons (DALY rate) due to exposure to ground-level ozone pollution.
epi-OZD-ah.name: Ozone
epi-OZD-ah.source: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation

epi-PMD-ah.def: We measure PM2.5 exposure using the number of age-standardized disability-adjusted life-years lost per 100,000 persons (DALY rate) due to exposure to fine air particulate matter smaller than 2.5 micrometers (PM2.5).
epi-PMD-ah.name: Ambient particulate matter pollution
epi-PMD-ah.source: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation
